# Shared exclude list, auto-discovered via `bca.toml`'s
# `exclude_from = ".bcaignore"`. Mirrors the deny-set the self-scan
# workflow and the local baseline refresh both walk. Keep this file and
# `.bca-baseline.toml` in sync — the baseline keys are sensitive to
# which files the walker visits.
#
# Patterns use the `./`-prefix convention. The walker re-anchors every
# seed to that form (#488), so these match the same files regardless of
# whether the root was spelled `.`, `$PWD`, or a manifest-resolved
# absolute path.
#
# Blank lines and lines whose first non-whitespace character is `#`
# are skipped (`.gitignore`-style).

./tree-sitter-*/**
./tests/**
./**/tests/**
./**/*_tests.rs
./enums/**
./target/**
./big-code-analysis-book/**
./docs/**
./packaging/**
./utils/**
./xtask/**
./generate-grammars/**
./man/**
./abuild-keys/**
./**/examples/**
./check-*.py
